l "ComponentLicensing" }{\f1\fs20 {\*\datafield 08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b02000000080000001300000043006f006d0070006f006e0065006e0074004c006900630065006e00730069006e0067000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs20\f1\fs20\ul\cf2 3.3.3}}}{\f1\fs20 )
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li720\ri720\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 The DMA
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  header files and other library definition elements are subject to this kind of license. 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 The purpose of the open-source library license is to allow libraries that are contributed, developed, and redistributed as open-source software to be employed in the \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
construction of closed-source software (whether freeware, shareware, or commercial software) and in the construction of new open-source software.\~
 However, any derivative work based on an open-source library that is itself a library is required to be an o\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 p\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 en-source library and satisfy other conditions of the open-source library license. \~
 In addition, there can be licensing conditions on the notification that must be provided concerning the use of open-source libraries in the composition of other open- and\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 closed-source software.

\par \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 The open-source library licenses distinguishes between creating derivative libraries and depending on libraries in the composition of non-library software.\~
 Allowing closed-source usage encourages interoperability, reduces redundanc\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
y of useful library implementations, and expands the community of application for the library, contributing to its achievement of high reliability and utility.\~
 It also provides an avenue for developers of close-source software to contribute useful librar\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 i\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
es to the open-source community and retain full rights to application of the library (and open-source improvements of it) in closed-source applications.
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li720\ri720\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \b\fs27\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs22 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 3.3.3 Open-Source Component Licensing
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li720\ri720\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
If necessary, there will also be a separate open-source component\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  license recommended for use with open-source DMAware components.\~ 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 Components, which are relatively-new kinds of software artifacts, have qualities of complete software elements and also of libraries.\~ The open-source component license is comparable in st\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
rength to the GNU Lesser General Public License [}{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 HYPERLINK\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  "" \\l "[LGPL]" }{\f1\fs20 {\*\datafield 
08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b0200000008000000070000005b004c00470050004c005d000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs20\f1\fs20\ul\cf2 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 LGPL}}}{\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
] and provides for open-source distribution of components: software elements that are not independently operable but are employed in conjunction with software system\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  elements and libraries.\~
 Open-source components are similar to open-source libraries except that combination with other elements occurs only in the course of processing operations and is ephemeral.\~ 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li1440\ri720\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls4\adjustright\rin720\lin1440\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs20 The component is packaged separately although it may be redistributed with other software and installed in conjunction with the installation of other software.\~ 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}The open-source components may be operated in conjunction with other components and software elements that are not themselves open-source software.\~ 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Derivative works of the open-source components are required by the license to be preserved as open-source software.\~ 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Substitutions of closed-source components that are not derivative works yet provide the same interfaces and functionality are all
owed, so long as the closed-source solution is clearly differentiated and cannot confused with the open-source component (and vice-versa).
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f3\fs20 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Redistribution of the open-source components, derivative or otherwise, must be accompanied by license-required identifications and notifications.\~
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li720\ri720\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
Open-source implementations of Java classes, of ActiveX components, DMA service elements, and similar package\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 d components benefit from this form of licensing. \~\~
 Components have emerged since the creation of the GNU GPL and LGLP licenses. The objective is to permit, at the option of the contributor, free comingling of closed-source and open-source components in \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 o
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 perations of open-source and closed-source systems without diluting the open-source license on the open-source components themselves. \~\~ 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 One of the key qualities of open-source components and open-source libraries is agreement on \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
standardization of interfaces and allowance for substitutability of open-source and closed-source elements that honor those interfaces.\~ The interface is preserved as equally available for use with either kind of implementation.\~
 Likewise, the application\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 of the interface in the construction of open- and closed-source software is not restricted.
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs48\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning36\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs40 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.\~ Contribution Procedures
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs28 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.1 License and Release Required
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li720\ri720\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs17\i\f1\fs20 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 The open-source nature of contributions will be clearly specified and be authoritative.}{\f1\fs20 
\par }{\cs19\b\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.1.1 }{\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 New contr\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 ibutions must be clearly packaged with appropriate open-source license statements.
\par }{\cs19\b\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.1.2}{\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
 New contributions must be accompanied by a formal release statement that attests to the authority of the contributor to make the contribution, that transfers copyright\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
 to AIIM International, and that asserts the absence of any encumbrance to the license.\~ The material will be distributed as open-source certified software.
\par }{\cs19\b\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.1.3}{\f1\fs20 \hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1  The DMAware clearinghouse will maintain records of the history of new contributions and modif\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
ications to contributions so that the origin of all material is readily auditable and confirmable.
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs28 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 4.2 Limitation to Open-Source and Public-Domain Materials
\par }\pard\plain \s18\ql \li720\ri720\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin720\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af28\hich\af28\dbch\af28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs17\i\f1\fs20 
\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 So that users of DMAware material are always clear on the usability of software obtained from the D\hich\af1\dbch\af28\loch\f1 
MAware clearinghouse, only open-source and public-domain software will be provided on the clearinghouse site.}{\f1\fs20 
